1
00:00:01.960 --> 00:00:05.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Captain's Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 54274.7.</i>

2
00:00:05.797 --> 00:00:07.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Lieutenant Torres</i>
<i>has finally convinced me</i>

3
00:00:08.008 --> 00:00:11.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>that I can't put off a major</i>
<i>maintenance overhaul any longer.</i>

4
00:00:11.428 --> 00:00:12.971 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We've set down on</i>
<i>an uninhabited planet,</i>

5
00:00:13.055 --> 00:00:15.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and I've sent shuttles</i>
<i>to search for supplies.</i>

6
00:00:16.642 --> 00:00:19.019 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- What about the impulse upgrades?
- Day after tomorrow.

7
00:00:19.102 --> 00:00:20.604 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Put a new phase compensator
on that relay.

8
00:00:20.687 --> 00:00:22.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Environmental control?

9
00:00:22.272 --> 00:00:24.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The thermal regulators
are still running a little hot.

10
00:00:24.358 --> 00:00:25.984 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Too bad we can't just keep
the windows open.

11
00:00:26.068 --> 00:00:27.402 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How long until the warp drive
is back on line?

12
00:00:27.486 --> 00:00:28.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Six days.

13
00:00:28.695 --> 00:00:30.113 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You sure you can't get it done
any faster?

14
00:00:30.197 --> 00:00:32.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, I don't like sitting
still any more than you do,

15
00:00:32.950 --> 00:00:35.077 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but repairs this extensive
take time.

16
00:00:35.702 --> 00:00:37.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[equipment powering down]

17
00:00:37.204 --> 00:00:39.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mendez, track down
that power drain.

18
00:00:39.331 --> 00:00:40.290 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Right away.

19
00:00:40.374 --> 00:00:41.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know this ship
has been through a lot,

20
00:00:41.542 --> 00:00:43.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but you told me this would
only take a few days.

21
00:00:43.752 --> 00:00:45.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That was before I discovered
the microfractures

22
00:00:45.712 --> 00:00:46.922 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in the starboard nacelle

23
00:00:47.005 --> 00:00:48.674 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the fused relays
in the main computer.

24
00:00:49.925 --> 00:00:51.009 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who did that?

25
00:00:53.136 --> 00:00:57.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I noticed a charge imbalance
in the EPS feed.

26
00:00:57.099 --> 00:00:58.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry if I...

27
00:00:58.767 --> 00:01:00.352 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It could have taken us hours
to find that.

28
00:01:01.270 --> 00:01:03.939 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have a tactical
systems report for you.

29
00:01:04.022 --> 00:01:05.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's from Commander Tuvok.

30
00:01:05.732 --> 00:01:09.319 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd say you're capable of a lot more
than delivering padds, Icheb.

31
00:01:09.403 --> 00:01:10.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Janeway]
I agree.

32
00:01:10.862 --> 00:01:14.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Until we get underway again,
he's assigned to you.

33
00:01:14.992 --> 00:01:18.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
With him on your team, maybe
you'll get this job done a little faster.

34
00:01:25.335 --> 00:01:26.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[snoring]

35
00:01:29.298 --> 00:01:30.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Neelix?

36
00:01:35.554 --> 00:01:36.597 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[alarm blares]

37
00:01:37.598 --> 00:01:39.975 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Rise and shine.
It's 0500.

38
00:01:40.058 --> 00:01:42.519 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Already?
Oh!

39
00:01:42.603 --> 00:01:44.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, I was dreaming
we found the dilithium

40
00:01:44.980 --> 00:01:46.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and were back aboard Voyager.

41
00:01:47.065 --> 00:01:49.693 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dreaming is
an accurate description.

42
00:01:50.611 --> 00:01:52.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Didn't we already
scan this nebula?

43
00:01:52.696 --> 00:01:54.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Four times.

44
00:01:54.573 --> 00:01:56.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought the Borg
were known for being thorough.

45
00:01:56.950 --> 00:02:00.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Borg value efficiency,
not redundancy.

46
00:02:00.454 --> 00:02:02.623 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've got a hunch
about this nebula.

47
00:02:02.706 --> 00:02:04.207 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's dilithium
in there somewhere.

48
00:02:04.291 --> 00:02:05.334 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[console beeping]

49
00:02:07.419 --> 00:02:09.713 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm getting some fluctuating
energy readings.

50
00:02:09.796 --> 00:02:11.048 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
From the nebula?

51
00:02:11.131 --> 00:02:12.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, it's weapons fire.

52
00:04:07.831 --> 00:04:09.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's get out of here.

53
00:04:09.458 --> 00:04:10.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're receiving a distress call.

54
00:04:10.959 --> 00:04:12.002 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[staticky]
...have casualties.

55
00:04:12.836 --> 00:04:14.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Please help us.

56
00:04:15.505 --> 00:04:19.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
We're on a humanitarian mission
delivering medical supplies.

57
00:04:24.765 --> 00:04:26.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Reverse course.

58
00:04:26.600 --> 00:04:27.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
We can't just leave them.

59
00:04:28.059 --> 00:04:29.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Starfleet policy.

60
00:04:29.561 --> 00:04:32.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Interference in alien conflicts
is strictly prohibited.

61
00:04:32.314 --> 00:04:34.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You heard their Captain.
It's a medical ship.

62
00:04:34.524 --> 00:04:36.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
- [beeping]
- Their shields are down.

63
00:04:36.359 --> 00:04:38.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Life support is failing
on at least three decks.

64
00:04:41.323 --> 00:04:42.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Open a channel to the other ship.

65
00:04:44.701 --> 00:04:46.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
This is Ensign Kim
of the Delta Flyer.

66
00:04:46.953 --> 00:04:50.123 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I don't know what you're fighting about,
but it looks like you've won.

67
00:04:50.207 --> 00:04:52.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
The people on the other ship
have casualties. We'd like to...

68
00:04:52.751 --> 00:04:54.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
This isn't your concern.

69
00:04:55.045 --> 00:04:58.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I'm not taking sides.
I only want to help the wounded.

70
00:04:58.173 --> 00:04:59.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[rumbling]

71
00:04:59.216 --> 00:05:01.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Withdraw immediately.

72
00:05:02.385 --> 00:05:03.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
They're charging weapons.

73
00:05:05.305 --> 00:05:08.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Neelix, set our deflector beam
for a narrow pulse.

74
00:05:08.225 --> 00:05:11.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Seven, let me know the second
their weapons array is fully charged.

75
00:05:11.353 --> 00:05:13.396 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I might be able to trigger
an overload.

76
00:05:13.480 --> 00:05:16.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[Neelix] The deflector bandwidth
is at .4 microns.

77
00:05:16.733 --> 00:05:17.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Now.

78
00:05:23.406 --> 00:05:26.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Their weapons are off-line.
Shields are down.

79
00:05:27.869 --> 00:05:29.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
They're retreating.

80
00:05:29.996 --> 00:05:32.332 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Take the helm.
Neelix, you're with me.

81
00:05:36.002 --> 00:05:38.255 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[staticky popping]

82
00:05:52.435 --> 00:05:54.604 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[groaning]

83
00:06:02.487 --> 00:06:03.697 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Who's in charge here?

84
00:06:04.363 --> 00:06:05.407 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
He is.

85
00:06:06.074 --> 00:06:07.701 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What are we going to do?

86
00:06:07.784 --> 00:06:09.578 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It's okay.
We're here to help.

87
00:06:09.661 --> 00:06:11.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
The ship that attacked you
is gone.

88
00:06:12.873 --> 00:06:13.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Who are you?

89
00:06:14.666 --> 00:06:16.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Harry Kim from
the Starship Voyager.

90
00:06:16.710 --> 00:06:18.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
We're responding
to your distress call.

91
00:06:19.004 --> 00:06:20.922 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
We can treat your wounded.

92
00:06:24.968 --> 00:06:26.303 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Captain?

93
00:06:26.385 --> 00:06:27.554 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dead, sir.

94
00:06:27.637 --> 00:06:29.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So are the rest
of the officers.

95
00:06:30.015 --> 00:06:33.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm reading a total
of 27 life-forms aboard the ship.

96
00:06:33.727 --> 00:06:35.186 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There were 56 of us.

97
00:06:35.270 --> 00:06:37.731 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How are we going to get home
without the officers?

98
00:06:37.814 --> 00:06:39.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We need to restore main power.

99
00:06:39.733 --> 00:06:41.192 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where's the warp interface?

100
00:06:41.276 --> 00:06:43.486 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're passengers,
not crewmen.

101
00:06:43.570 --> 00:06:46.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can access
engineering systems from here.

102
00:06:51.077 --> 00:06:52.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

103
00:06:56.166 --> 00:06:58.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Kim]
Your warp core's intact.

104
00:06:58.793 --> 00:07:01.171 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think I can bring it
back on line.

105
00:07:01.254 --> 00:07:02.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Can you monitor
antimatter flow?

106
00:07:03.548 --> 00:07:04.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not sure. I...

107
00:07:04.841 --> 00:07:09.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just watch this readout,
and tell me if it starts to fluctuate.

108
00:07:13.892 --> 00:07:16.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[core powering up]

109
00:07:19.773 --> 00:07:22.192 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Kim] I'm routing emergency power
to structural integrity.

110
00:07:23.485 --> 00:07:25.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Atmospheric pressure
is returning to normal.

111
00:07:28.573 --> 00:07:31.826 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Neelix, we'll go through the ship
deck by deck-- find the survivors.

112
00:07:31.910 --> 00:07:34.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We need to get our cloak
back on line.

113
00:07:34.245 --> 00:07:36.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll take a look at it as soon
as I've repaired the engines.

114
00:07:36.748 --> 00:07:38.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No. The cloak
is more important.

115
00:07:38.625 --> 00:07:41.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Annari have far more powerful
weapons than we do.

116
00:07:41.461 --> 00:07:44.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If they come back,
the cloak is our best defense.

117
00:07:45.048 --> 00:07:46.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'll try to get it
back on line.

118
00:07:52.514 --> 00:07:55.100 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Kim to Delta Flyer.
- [Seven] Go ahead.

119
00:07:55.183 --> 00:07:56.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I need your help, Seven.

120
00:07:56.977 --> 00:07:58.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It looks like we're going
to be here for awhile.

121
00:08:02.023 --> 00:08:03.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How did you do it?

122
00:08:03.358 --> 00:08:04.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Kim] Do what?

123
00:08:04.859 --> 00:08:06.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Disable the Annari warship
so quickly?

124
00:08:07.445 --> 00:08:10.573 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh, basically, we used
their own weapons against them.

125
00:08:10.657 --> 00:08:11.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How?

126
00:08:12.867 --> 00:08:15.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We used a deflector pulse
to overload their phaser banks.

127
00:08:16.663 --> 00:08:17.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[power whirring on]

128
00:08:17.998 --> 00:08:19.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

129
00:08:19.916 --> 00:08:21.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know a lot
about engineering.

130
00:08:22.585 --> 00:08:24.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's all part
of my Starfleet training.

131
00:08:24.796 --> 00:08:25.839 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Starfleet?

132
00:08:25.922 --> 00:08:28.174 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah. The organization
I work for.

133
00:08:28.258 --> 00:08:30.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And they teach you
all these things?

134
00:08:30.176 --> 00:08:31.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We train at an academy,

135
00:08:31.553 --> 00:08:34.472 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I guess I've picked up
a few new tricks

136
00:08:34.556 --> 00:08:36.391 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
during my time on Voyager.

137
00:08:36.474 --> 00:08:38.143 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How long have you been Captain?

138
00:08:38.226 --> 00:08:39.352 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

139
00:08:39.436 --> 00:08:40.770 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm just an Ensign.

140
00:08:40.854 --> 00:08:42.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ensign? E... What's that?

141
00:08:42.981 --> 00:08:44.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A junior officer.

142
00:08:45.525 --> 00:08:48.361 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The lowest ranked officer,
actually.

143
00:08:50.989 --> 00:08:53.074 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is my first
deep space assignment.

144
00:08:54.284 --> 00:08:56.036 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It hasn't gone very well.

145
00:08:58.621 --> 00:08:59.789 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Could you hand me that?

146
00:09:02.542 --> 00:09:04.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My first week on the job
didn't go very well, either.

147
00:09:05.670 --> 00:09:08.548 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We ended up 70,000
light-years from home,

148
00:09:08.631 --> 00:09:11.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
lost over a dozen crew members,

149
00:09:11.801 --> 00:09:14.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I got through it,
and so will you.

150
00:09:17.599 --> 00:09:18.975 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hope so.

151
00:09:20.060 --> 00:09:22.562 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you're going to be
a starship officer,

152
00:09:22.645 --> 00:09:25.940 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you've got to accept that
adversity comes with the job.

153
00:09:40.205 --> 00:09:41.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's that?

154
00:09:41.748 --> 00:09:43.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's a diagnostic
of the antimatter injectors.

155
00:09:43.917 --> 00:09:46.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, I meant that stuff
you're eating.

156
00:09:46.878 --> 00:09:48.004 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nutritional supplements,

157
00:09:48.088 --> 00:09:50.381 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
replicated to meet
my metabolic requirements.

158
00:09:50.465 --> 00:09:51.674 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sounds delicious.

159
00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:56.304 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know,
in the Mess Hall,

160
00:09:56.387 --> 00:09:58.807 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
they actually have tables
and chairs for that.

161
00:09:59.766 --> 00:10:01.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I prefer to work while I eat.

162
00:10:01.726 --> 00:10:03.770 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's a more efficient use
of my time.

163
00:10:06.898 --> 00:10:08.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You did a great job today.

164
00:10:09.609 --> 00:10:12.153 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're ahead of schedule
thanks to you.

165
00:10:14.405 --> 00:10:16.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Here's what we're going
to work on tomorrow.

166
00:10:18.660 --> 00:10:20.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll see you at 0600.

167
00:10:26.876 --> 00:10:27.919 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Icheb.

168
00:10:28.878 --> 00:10:30.255 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes?

169
00:10:30.338 --> 00:10:31.589 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do you do for fun?

170
00:10:32.340 --> 00:10:35.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Fun?
- Recreation.

171
00:10:35.260 --> 00:10:37.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How do you spend your time
when you're off duty?

172
00:10:37.428 --> 00:10:41.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Between my work and my studies,
I don't have much time for recreation.

173
00:10:41.766 --> 00:10:45.311 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've learned that you've got
to take a break once in awhile.

174
00:10:46.146 --> 00:10:48.940 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been doing a lot
of rock climbing on the holodeck.

175
00:10:49.023 --> 00:10:52.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe when we're finished
tightening all the nuts and bolts,

176
00:10:52.318 --> 00:10:53.528 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
you'd like to join me.

177
00:10:54.696 --> 00:10:56.948 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I do have an interest
in geology.

178
00:10:58.158 --> 00:10:59.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not about the rocks, Icheb.

179
00:10:59.951 --> 00:11:01.536 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's about the climbing.

180
00:11:09.794 --> 00:11:11.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Main power
has been restored.

181
00:11:11.379 --> 00:11:13.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All stations responding.

182
00:11:13.965 --> 00:11:15.466 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The cloak's back on line.

183
00:11:16.259 --> 00:11:18.344 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Impulse and warp drives
are standing by.

184
00:11:19.095 --> 00:11:20.597 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shields are at 96 percent.

185
00:11:20.722 --> 00:11:22.849 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd say you're ready
to get back on course.

186
00:11:22.932 --> 00:11:24.225 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We appreciate your help.

187
00:11:24.309 --> 00:11:27.020 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- I hope you have a safe journey.
- Mr. Kim...

188
00:11:28.396 --> 00:11:31.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I feel guilty
asking even more of you,

189
00:11:31.441 --> 00:11:34.068 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but no one on this ship
knows how to fly it.

190
00:11:35.528 --> 00:11:38.781 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
None of you
has ever piloted a starship?

191
00:11:38.865 --> 00:11:42.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've trained in shuttles,
but nothing like this.

192
00:11:43.369 --> 00:11:44.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

193
00:11:45.121 --> 00:11:48.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll enter a flight plan
in the auto-navigation system

194
00:11:48.625 --> 00:11:51.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and give you a quick course
in helm operations.

195
00:11:51.336 --> 00:11:52.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You shouldn't have any trouble.

196
00:11:52.879 --> 00:11:53.838 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Couldn't you take us?

197
00:11:54.422 --> 00:11:57.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This ship needs an experienced
commanding officer.

198
00:11:57.634 --> 00:12:00.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sorry, but we've already gotten
more involved than we should have,

199
00:12:00.719 --> 00:12:02.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and they need us back on Voyager.

200
00:12:02.388 --> 00:12:04.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's not just my ship
that concerns me.

201
00:12:04.641 --> 00:12:07.060 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've made an enemy
of the Annari now,

202
00:12:07.143 --> 00:12:09.103 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but if you dock your ship
in our Shuttle Bay

203
00:12:09.187 --> 00:12:10.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
our cloak will protect you.

204
00:12:11.064 --> 00:12:13.483 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's a generous offer,
but we'll be fine.

205
00:12:13.566 --> 00:12:15.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Please, Mr. Kim,
we can't afford to fail.

206
00:12:17.195 --> 00:12:19.697 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- This ship is...
- Loken, don't.

207
00:12:20.823 --> 00:12:22.325 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We can trust these people.

208
00:12:24.244 --> 00:12:25.536 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Loken]
I'm a doctor.

209
00:12:26.454 --> 00:12:28.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
These people
are my research team.

210
00:12:29.082 --> 00:12:31.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're carrying new vaccines
to our homeland.

211
00:12:31.251 --> 00:12:32.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They'll save thousands of lives.

212
00:12:33.503 --> 00:12:36.547 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sir, I looked at their flight plan.

213
00:12:36.631 --> 00:12:39.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It takes them pretty
close to Voyager.

214
00:12:42.387 --> 00:12:44.806 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll bring you
as far as our ship.

215
00:12:44.889 --> 00:12:46.307 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
When we get there,

216
00:12:46.391 --> 00:12:48.977 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you can discuss your situation
with my Captain.

217
00:12:49.060 --> 00:12:50.353 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you.

218
00:12:51.396 --> 00:12:52.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What about
Starfleet policy?

219
00:12:53.815 --> 00:12:55.817 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is a humanitarian
mission.

220
00:12:56.651 --> 00:12:58.444 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dock the Flyer
in their Shuttle Bay.

221
00:13:07.036 --> 00:13:08.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're approaching the planet.

222
00:13:08.955 --> 00:13:10.623 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Take us out of warp.

223
00:13:10.707 --> 00:13:12.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Disengage the cloak.
- Wait.

224
00:13:13.835 --> 00:13:16.087 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm detecting three
alien vessels in orbit.

225
00:13:17.380 --> 00:13:18.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On screen.

226
00:13:21.050 --> 00:13:22.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Crewman]
Those are Annari warships.

227
00:13:22.844 --> 00:13:24.554 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your people are in danger.

228
00:13:37.859 --> 00:13:39.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I apologize
for the state of my ship.

229
00:13:39.818 --> 00:13:42.155 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- We weren't expecting company.
- I hope we're not imposing.

230
00:13:42.238 --> 00:13:43.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not at all.

231
00:13:43.406 --> 00:13:45.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Making contact with new cultures
is a priority for us.

232
00:13:45.992 --> 00:13:47.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
For us, too.

233
00:13:47.826 --> 00:13:49.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is a fine ship, Captain.

234
00:13:49.412 --> 00:13:51.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
One of the best in the fleet,
but it could use

235
00:13:51.914 --> 00:13:54.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a new set of deuterium injectors.

236
00:13:54.125 --> 00:13:55.918 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Any chance you could
provide them?

237
00:13:56.919 --> 00:13:58.713 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think we can arrange something.

238
00:13:59.672 --> 00:14:01.174 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What are you offering
in exchange?

239
00:14:01.257 --> 00:14:02.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Zeolitic ore.

240
00:14:02.383 --> 00:14:04.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We mined several tons of it
from an asteroid field.

241
00:14:04.761 --> 00:14:06.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's high-grade, easy to refine.

242
00:14:07.013 --> 00:14:09.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll speak to my supply officer.

243
00:14:09.098 --> 00:14:10.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[console beeps]

244
00:14:10.224 --> 00:14:12.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're being hailed
by Ensign Kim, audio only.

245
00:14:13.311 --> 00:14:14.604 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello, Harry.

246
00:14:14.687 --> 00:14:17.148 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- <i>Is everything all right?</i>
- Of course. Why wouldn't it be?

247
00:14:17.231 --> 00:14:21.944 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our long-range scans detected
several alien ships orbiting the planet.

248
00:14:22.028 --> 00:14:24.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I appreciate your concern,
but there's nothing to worry about.

249
00:14:24.447 --> 00:14:26.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We've made some new friends,
that's all.

250
00:14:26.240 --> 00:14:27.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
When can we expect you back?

251
00:14:28.242 --> 00:14:29.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We've run into a slight delay.

252
00:14:30.078 --> 00:14:31.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Nothing serious, I hope.</i>

253
00:14:31.537 --> 00:14:33.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No. Everything's under control.

254
00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:34.749 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Good.</i>

255
00:14:34.832 --> 00:14:36.918 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Any luck finding dilithium?

256
00:14:37.001 --> 00:14:38.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Uh, I'm afraid not.</i>

257
00:14:38.378 --> 00:14:40.046 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll tell the other teams
to keep looking.

258
00:14:40.129 --> 00:14:42.548 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- See you soon, Ensign.
- <i>Yes, ma'am. Kim out.</i>

259
00:14:42.632 --> 00:14:44.258 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dilithium...

260
00:14:44.342 --> 00:14:45.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We can get that
for you, too.

261
00:14:46.052 --> 00:14:47.095 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really?

262
00:14:48.304 --> 00:14:50.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She's formed an alliance
with our enemy.

263
00:14:51.766 --> 00:14:54.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just because they're talking
doesn't mean they formed an alliance.

264
00:14:54.644 --> 00:14:56.687 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's probably just
a friendly meeting.

265
00:14:56.771 --> 00:14:58.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's how the Annari operate.

266
00:14:58.481 --> 00:15:01.818 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They come to you as friends,
and when they've won your trust,

267
00:15:01.901 --> 00:15:04.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
they declare you subjects
of the Annari Empire.

268
00:15:09.659 --> 00:15:11.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Kim to Voyager.</i>

269
00:15:11.202 --> 00:15:13.121 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We didn't expect you so soon.

270
00:15:13.204 --> 00:15:15.373 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Actually, Captain,</i>
<i>I'm closer than I let on,</i>

271
00:15:15.456 --> 00:15:17.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and I've brought</i>
<i>some new friends of my own.</i>

272
00:15:20.086 --> 00:15:23.381 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our chances of getting home
without your help aren't very good.

273
00:15:24.715 --> 00:15:26.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'd appreciate any assistance
you could offer.

274
00:15:26.926 --> 00:15:28.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hope you understand.

275
00:15:29.137 --> 00:15:31.055 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I need to give this some thought.

276
00:15:42.859 --> 00:15:45.278 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've put me in
a difficult position, Ensign.

277
00:15:46.070 --> 00:15:48.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We could use the help
the Annari are offering,

278
00:15:48.114 --> 00:15:50.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but if they find out
we're aiding their enemy...

279
00:15:50.408 --> 00:15:52.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I couldn't just stand by
and do nothing.

280
00:15:52.493 --> 00:15:55.496 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That doesn't justify getting involved
in somebody else's fight.

281
00:15:56.414 --> 00:15:57.915 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What would you
have done?

282
00:15:58.040 --> 00:16:00.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Probably exactly what you did.

283
00:16:00.084 --> 00:16:02.003 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I guess I learned from the best.

284
00:16:02.086 --> 00:16:04.881 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If this were simply an errand
of mercy, I wouldn't hesitate.

285
00:16:04.964 --> 00:16:08.759 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But the fact is, these people
are involved in an interplanetary war.

286
00:16:08.843 --> 00:16:12.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, I've gotten to know them
over the last couple of days.

287
00:16:12.722 --> 00:16:14.098 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You met Loken.

288
00:16:14.182 --> 00:16:16.225 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're scientists, not soldiers.

289
00:16:16.309 --> 00:16:18.227 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've only heard
one side of the story.

290
00:16:18.311 --> 00:16:19.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You've taken sides before.

291
00:16:19.979 --> 00:16:21.939 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Borg resistance,
the Vaadwaur...

292
00:16:22.023 --> 00:16:23.858 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Those were
different circumstances.

293
00:16:23.941 --> 00:16:25.776 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You were trying to help people
in need.

294
00:16:25.860 --> 00:16:27.361 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How is this any different?

295
00:16:28.279 --> 00:16:30.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have you thought about applying
to the Advocate General's office?

296
00:16:30.948 --> 00:16:32.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You'd make a good lawyer.

297
00:16:33.784 --> 00:16:35.077 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

298
00:16:35.161 --> 00:16:38.080 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I suppose I could spare
Chakotay or Tuvok for a few days.

299
00:16:38.164 --> 00:16:39.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That won't be necessary.

300
00:16:41.876 --> 00:16:43.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Kraylor know me.
They trust me.

301
00:16:44.754 --> 00:16:47.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sure they'd find Tuvok
or Chakotay just as trustworthy.

302
00:16:48.966 --> 00:16:50.885 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But they outrank me.

303
00:16:50.968 --> 00:16:53.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you send one of them,
it won't be my mission anymore.

304
00:16:54.639 --> 00:16:55.681 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your mission.

305
00:16:55.765 --> 00:16:57.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My first real command.

306
00:16:57.892 --> 00:16:59.852 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've been in command
on Voyager before.

307
00:16:59.936 --> 00:17:02.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
On the night shift,
for a few hours...

308
00:17:02.271 --> 00:17:03.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not the same thing.

309
00:17:03.898 --> 00:17:06.234 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You and Chakotay are always
a couple of decks away,

310
00:17:06.317 --> 00:17:09.028 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
ready to take over
if anything goes wrong.

311
00:17:09.111 --> 00:17:11.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been on Voyager
for almost seven years,

312
00:17:11.489 --> 00:17:12.823 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and I'm still an Ensign.

313
00:17:12.907 --> 00:17:15.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If this is your way
of bucking for a promotion...

314
00:17:15.826 --> 00:17:19.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, no, I understand
there's a command structure

315
00:17:19.997 --> 00:17:21.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and that our circumstances
are unique.

316
00:17:21.749 --> 00:17:24.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But the fact is,
if we were back home,

317
00:17:24.961 --> 00:17:26.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd be a Lieutenant by now,

318
00:17:26.837 --> 00:17:28.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
maybe even
a Lieutenant Commander.

319
00:17:29.257 --> 00:17:31.509 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're pretty sure
of yourself, aren't you?

320
00:17:31.592 --> 00:17:33.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I know I can do this,

321
00:17:33.636 --> 00:17:36.138 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the Kraylor are giving me
a chance to prove it.

322
00:17:38.349 --> 00:17:41.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I expect you back before
we complete our repairs.

323
00:17:41.519 --> 00:17:42.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, ma'am.

324
00:17:42.895 --> 00:17:44.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I'm not
sending you alone.

325
00:17:44.981 --> 00:17:47.775 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Captain.
- I want you to take Seven.

326
00:17:47.858 --> 00:17:51.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Since she has no rank,
you clearly outrank her.

327
00:17:59.954 --> 00:18:03.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Lieutenant Torres asked me to repair
a malfunctioning holo-emitter.

328
00:18:03.499 --> 00:18:04.709 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs]
It's about time.

329
00:18:05.793 --> 00:18:07.628 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Whenever I move
to the far corner

330
00:18:07.712 --> 00:18:10.590 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of the Surgical Bay,
my legs disappear.

331
00:18:15.428 --> 00:18:18.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Seven of Nine told me
you gave her social lessons.

332
00:18:18.806 --> 00:18:21.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hmm. She wanted to get along
better with the crew.

333
00:18:21.601 --> 00:18:25.062 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Social skills are one thing
the Borg never assimilated.

334
00:18:25.730 --> 00:18:27.690 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was hoping
you could instruct me, as well.

335
00:18:27.773 --> 00:18:29.025 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd be delighted.

336
00:18:29.108 --> 00:18:30.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Lesson One:
"Making a First Impression."

337
00:18:30.985 --> 00:18:33.654 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Actually, I wanted to ask you
about something specific.

338
00:18:33.738 --> 00:18:34.780 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fire away.

339
00:18:35.573 --> 00:18:37.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How can you tell
when someone has...

340
00:18:38.075 --> 00:18:40.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
romantic feelings for you?

341
00:18:40.995 --> 00:18:44.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Icheb, this <i>is </i>a surprise.

342
00:18:44.123 --> 00:18:45.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have you caught
someone's eye?

343
00:18:47.168 --> 00:18:48.753 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm speaking hypothetically.

344
00:18:48.836 --> 00:18:50.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ah.

345
00:18:50.671 --> 00:18:51.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[clears throat]

346
00:18:52.340 --> 00:18:53.674 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hypothetically,

347
00:18:53.758 --> 00:18:57.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
there are various indications
of romantic attraction.

348
00:18:57.428 --> 00:19:02.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Compliments, for example,
invitations to social activities,

349
00:19:02.350 --> 00:19:05.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
finding excuses to be
in close proximity with someone.

350
00:19:05.895 --> 00:19:09.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes, but couldn't those things happen
in a relationship that wasn't romantic?

351
00:19:10.024 --> 00:19:11.317 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I suppose.

352
00:19:11.400 --> 00:19:13.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Is there a way
to be absolutely certain?

353
00:19:13.611 --> 00:19:17.239 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, short of an open
declaration of affection,

354
00:19:17.323 --> 00:19:20.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
there are some fairly reliable
physiological responses:

355
00:19:20.534 --> 00:19:24.622 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
elevated blood pressure, increased
beta-endorphin production...

356
00:19:24.705 --> 00:19:27.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thank you, Doctor.
You've been very helpful.

357
00:19:28.334 --> 00:19:30.169 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
With my guidance,
you will master the nuances

358
00:19:30.252 --> 00:19:32.088 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of social interaction
in no time!

359
00:19:34.423 --> 00:19:35.466 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Paris]
Harry!

360
00:19:36.425 --> 00:19:37.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs]
Take me with you, buddy.

361
00:19:37.927 --> 00:19:39.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sorry, Tom.
This is my mission.

362
00:19:39.845 --> 00:19:42.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, come on, I've been itching
to get back into space

363
00:19:42.515 --> 00:19:44.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
ever since we set down
on this dust bowl.

364
00:19:44.684 --> 00:19:47.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm tired of cleaning conduits
and replacing relays.

365
00:19:47.478 --> 00:19:50.690 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're a married man now.
You've got family responsibilities.

366
00:19:50.773 --> 00:19:53.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just leave the away missions
to the young, unattached guys.

367
00:19:53.359 --> 00:19:55.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That ship is in pretty bad shape.
You're going to need a good pilot.

368
00:19:55.778 --> 00:19:56.987 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, thanks.

369
00:19:57.071 --> 00:19:58.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wait a minute...

370
00:19:59.490 --> 00:20:01.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I know what this is about.

371
00:20:01.283 --> 00:20:02.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You do?

372
00:20:02.493 --> 00:20:05.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sure. You've got a girl on that ship
you don't want me to know about.

373
00:20:05.996 --> 00:20:07.289 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughing]

374
00:20:07.373 --> 00:20:08.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's no girl.
Not this time.

375
00:20:10.292 --> 00:20:11.377 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then what is it?

376
00:20:11.460 --> 00:20:12.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

377
00:20:12.586 --> 00:20:15.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't know how else to say this,
so I'll just say it.

378
00:20:15.172 --> 00:20:17.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've always been
Captain Proton.

379
00:20:17.216 --> 00:20:19.009 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have always been Buster Kincaid.

380
00:20:19.635 --> 00:20:21.137 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's my turn this time.

381
00:20:24.724 --> 00:20:26.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[indistinct chatter]

382
00:20:34.900 --> 00:20:38.696 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm glad you're not planning to leave
on an empty stomach, "Captain."

383
00:20:39.447 --> 00:20:42.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have plomeek soup
and eggplant parmesan.

384
00:20:42.366 --> 00:20:44.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Either's fine.
- Wrong answer.

385
00:20:44.618 --> 00:20:45.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Excuse me?

386
00:20:45.745 --> 00:20:49.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you're going to be a Captain,
you have to act like a Captain.

387
00:20:49.498 --> 00:20:51.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Never admit you're
uncertain about anything.

388
00:20:52.001 --> 00:20:54.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can't be indecisive
in front of your crew.

389
00:20:54.545 --> 00:20:56.839 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's just a snack, Neelix.

390
00:20:56.922 --> 00:20:59.258 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When Captain Janeway
comes in here,

391
00:20:59.341 --> 00:21:01.385 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
she knows exactly
what she wants.

392
00:21:01.469 --> 00:21:03.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe I'm just not as picky
about my food.

393
00:21:04.722 --> 00:21:07.850 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Whatever you say... Ensign.

394
00:21:08.350 --> 00:21:09.185 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Neelix.

395
00:21:11.520 --> 00:21:13.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Plomeek soup,
and make sure it's hot.

396
00:21:22.490 --> 00:21:24.116 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Captain on the Bridge.

397
00:21:25.701 --> 00:21:27.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where did you learn that?

398
00:21:27.286 --> 00:21:29.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been studying
that Starfleet manual you loaned me.

399
00:21:30.039 --> 00:21:31.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Take your station,
Mr. Terek.

400
00:21:31.582 --> 00:21:32.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Aye, sir.

401
00:21:33.793 --> 00:21:34.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Course?

402
00:21:35.044 --> 00:21:36.086 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll do it.

403
00:21:36.796 --> 00:21:40.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Laying in a course,
heading 115 mark 37.

404
00:21:42.384 --> 00:21:44.303 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Does this ship
have a name?

405
00:21:44.386 --> 00:21:47.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Medical Transport 136.

406
00:21:47.306 --> 00:21:49.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think we can do
better than that.

407
00:21:53.395 --> 00:21:54.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nightingale.

408
00:21:56.023 --> 00:21:57.983 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The name of someone
from my homeworld.

409
00:21:58.067 --> 00:22:01.070 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She was famous for treating
wounded soldiers on the battlefield.

410
00:22:02.363 --> 00:22:03.864 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's perfect.

411
00:22:03.948 --> 00:22:04.990 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hail Voyager.

412
00:22:06.575 --> 00:22:07.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[communications beep]

413
00:22:08.244 --> 00:22:10.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Kim to Voyager.
We're ready to get underway.

414
00:22:10.871 --> 00:22:12.414 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Janeway]
<i>Acknowledged. Good luck.</i>

415
00:22:13.582 --> 00:22:15.584 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
See you in a few days.
Kim out.

416
00:22:15.668 --> 00:22:16.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Main power.

417
00:22:16.794 --> 00:22:18.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- On line.
- Tactical.

418
00:22:18.629 --> 00:22:21.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Shields and weapons
standing by.

419
00:22:22.383 --> 00:22:23.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Bring the cloak on line.

420
00:22:24.844 --> 00:22:26.846 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Warp 6.

421
00:22:28.597 --> 00:22:30.599 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Engage.

422
00:22:40.192 --> 00:22:44.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Kim] <i>Acting Captain's Personal Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 54277.3.</i>

423
00:22:44.989 --> 00:22:46.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>My first day in command</i>
<i>has been challenging,</i>

424
00:22:46.991 --> 00:22:49.076 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>but I've loved</i>
<i>every minute of it.</i>

425
00:22:49.159 --> 00:22:52.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I can't help feeling that this was</i>
<i>something I was born to do.</i>

426
00:22:53.330 --> 00:22:56.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The hourly status report
you requested.

427
00:22:56.792 --> 00:22:57.835 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks.

428
00:22:58.669 --> 00:23:00.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why have you brought
these items aboard?

429
00:23:01.046 --> 00:23:03.340 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They make me
feel more at home.

430
00:23:03.424 --> 00:23:05.634 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'll only be on this vessel
for a few days.

431
00:23:05.718 --> 00:23:08.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Decorating is an inefficient
use of your time.

432
00:23:08.304 --> 00:23:10.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's important to forge
a personal connection

433
00:23:10.973 --> 00:23:13.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
with your vessel;
make the ship your own.

434
00:23:13.434 --> 00:23:14.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ask Captain Janeway.

435
00:23:14.894 --> 00:23:17.646 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll discuss it with her
the moment we return.

436
00:23:20.357 --> 00:23:21.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is there anything else?

437
00:23:21.650 --> 00:23:23.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I asked Terek
to make a course correction.

438
00:23:23.652 --> 00:23:25.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's never done that before.

439
00:23:25.362 --> 00:23:27.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd better check on him.

440
00:23:27.197 --> 00:23:29.950 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I believe he's capable
of doing it himself.

441
00:23:31.535 --> 00:23:32.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

442
00:23:37.499 --> 00:23:38.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Status?

443
00:23:38.626 --> 00:23:39.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've entered the new heading.

444
00:23:40.753 --> 00:23:43.881 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Looks like the guidance vector
is off by a couple of microns.

445
00:23:43.964 --> 00:23:45.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was about to correct that.

446
00:23:45.966 --> 00:23:49.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You need to realign
the primary navigational sensor first.

447
00:23:49.595 --> 00:23:50.971 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

448
00:23:51.889 --> 00:23:54.767 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And make sure it stays locked
on your guide star.

449
00:23:54.850 --> 00:23:56.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Here, let me show you.

450
00:24:09.782 --> 00:24:11.075 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm-I'm sorry, Lieutenant.

451
00:24:11.158 --> 00:24:12.534 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't worry about it.

452
00:24:12.618 --> 00:24:14.703 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bumping elbows
comes with the job,

453
00:24:14.787 --> 00:24:16.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and you can call me B'Elanna.

454
00:24:17.581 --> 00:24:18.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Put this with the others.

455
00:24:22.044 --> 00:24:24.421 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
These relays should have been
replaced a while ago.

456
00:24:24.505 --> 00:24:26.548 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's amazing
they've held up this long.

457
00:24:27.633 --> 00:24:30.052 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I am really looking forward
to our climb.

458
00:24:31.637 --> 00:24:34.932 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Wouldn't you prefer to spend
your free time with your husband?

459
00:24:35.015 --> 00:24:36.058 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

460
00:24:36.809 --> 00:24:39.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If it doesn't involve
a race car, a shuttle,

461
00:24:39.353 --> 00:24:41.730 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
or something else he can drive,
Tom's not interested.

462
00:24:41.814 --> 00:24:46.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Besides, since we got married,
I see more than enough of him.

463
00:24:46.443 --> 00:24:47.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hold still.

464
00:24:58.789 --> 00:24:59.832 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[alarm beeps]

465
00:24:59.915 --> 00:25:00.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's that?

466
00:25:01.000 --> 00:25:03.419 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm reading a power fluctuation
somewhere in the propulsion system.

467
00:25:03.501 --> 00:25:05.796 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- It's destabilizing the cloak.
- All stop.

468
00:25:16.056 --> 00:25:17.099 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Core is stable.

469
00:25:17.683 --> 00:25:19.601 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That should take care of it.

470
00:25:19.685 --> 00:25:21.020 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you absolutely certain?

471
00:25:22.438 --> 00:25:23.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
As a scientist, you should know

472
00:25:23.856 --> 00:25:25.983 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
there's no such thing
as absolute certainty.

473
00:25:26.066 --> 00:25:27.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Perhaps we could run
a diagnostic before we...

474
00:25:27.985 --> 00:25:29.069 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That would take hours.

475
00:25:29.153 --> 00:25:32.322 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain Janeway wants us back
before Voyager finishes its overhaul.

476
00:25:32.406 --> 00:25:35.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The cloaking system is delicate.
It requires constant attention.

477
00:25:35.492 --> 00:25:37.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Correct me if I'm wrong,
you're a physician.

478
00:25:39.288 --> 00:25:41.081 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have to trust me on this.

479
00:25:41.165 --> 00:25:43.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'll monitor it closely.
Don't worry.

480
00:25:43.709 --> 00:25:48.005 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I simply want to ensure
that our mission is a success.

481
00:25:48.088 --> 00:25:50.466 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You asked me
to take command of this ship,

482
00:25:50.548 --> 00:25:52.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and that's what I'm doing.

483
00:25:59.933 --> 00:26:01.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tell Terek to resume course.

484
00:26:07.649 --> 00:26:10.611 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've discovered a serious flaw
in one of the ship's systems.

485
00:26:10.694 --> 00:26:12.863 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Which one?
- The Captain.

486
00:26:14.990 --> 00:26:17.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Captain's main function
is to issue orders, correct?

487
00:26:17.826 --> 00:26:19.577 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Right.
- And the crew's function

488
00:26:19.661 --> 00:26:22.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is to support the Captain
and carry out those orders.

489
00:26:22.831 --> 00:26:23.957 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's your point?

490
00:26:24.041 --> 00:26:26.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Every time you give an order,
you carry it out yourself.

491
00:26:26.835 --> 00:26:29.421 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And when someone else
makes a suggestion, you dismiss it.

492
00:26:29.505 --> 00:26:31.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
These people are inexperienced.

493
00:26:31.589 --> 00:26:32.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They need my help.

494
00:26:32.883 --> 00:26:36.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When you first came aboard Voyager,
did Captain Janeway help you?

495
00:26:37.304 --> 00:26:39.348 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sure. She looked after
all the junior officers.

496
00:26:39.431 --> 00:26:41.058 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
By doing your work for you?

497
00:26:41.141 --> 00:26:42.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No. She gave me a lot to do,
actually.

498
00:26:44.061 --> 00:26:46.355 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because she felt you were
more capable than she was?

499
00:26:46.438 --> 00:26:48.148 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course not.

500
00:26:48.232 --> 00:26:51.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She wanted me to learn,
to gain confidence.

501
00:26:53.195 --> 00:26:54.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Interesting.

502
00:27:05.124 --> 00:27:06.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Emergency power.

503
00:27:06.542 --> 00:27:09.253 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Repolarize the containment field.
- I can't.

504
00:27:09.336 --> 00:27:10.838 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The cloak is going to fail again.

505
00:27:10.921 --> 00:27:12.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't panic.
This is a minor malfunction.

506
00:27:12.548 --> 00:27:14.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Minor? We're losing
our main defense system.

507
00:27:14.591 --> 00:27:16.051 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- [alarm sounds]
- [Terek] We've been detected.

508
00:27:17.970 --> 00:27:20.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Two Annari vessels are
closing on our position.

509
00:27:20.597 --> 00:27:23.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Correction--
six Annari vessels.

510
00:27:29.231 --> 00:27:30.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[rumbling, alarm sounds]

511
00:27:31.024 --> 00:27:32.234 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Evasive maneuvers!

512
00:27:33.360 --> 00:27:34.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Kim to Engineering.

513
00:27:35.571 --> 00:27:36.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Go ahead.

514
00:27:37.489 --> 00:27:39.116 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We need that cloak
back on line.

515
00:27:39.199 --> 00:27:40.701 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The primary generator
has failed.

516
00:27:41.493 --> 00:27:42.536 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm trying to...

517
00:27:42.619 --> 00:27:43.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[yells]

518
00:27:44.788 --> 00:27:45.831 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Kim]
<i>Seven?</i>

519
00:27:47.332 --> 00:27:48.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Seven, come in.

520
00:27:49.626 --> 00:27:50.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have the Bridge.

521
00:27:50.878 --> 00:27:53.130 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- We need you here.
- I'll go, sir.

522
00:27:55.132 --> 00:27:57.634 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All right. I'll give you
instructions over the com.

523
00:27:59.094 --> 00:28:00.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Charge phaser banks.

524
00:28:00.888 --> 00:28:02.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Target their weapons array.

525
00:28:02.222 --> 00:28:03.348 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which ship?

526
00:28:03.432 --> 00:28:06.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The closest one,
off our port bow.

527
00:28:16.445 --> 00:28:17.529 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

528
00:28:17.613 --> 00:28:19.156 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dayla to the Bridge.

529
00:28:19.239 --> 00:28:20.782 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Life support's failing
down here.

530
00:28:20.866 --> 00:28:22.075 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I've gotten everyone out.</i>

531
00:28:23.452 --> 00:28:24.494 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good work.

532
00:28:24.870 --> 00:28:26.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now go
to the cloaking generator.

533
00:28:26.622 --> 00:28:28.373 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>What's the field polarity?</i>

534
00:28:28.457 --> 00:28:30.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
206.4.

535
00:28:30.209 --> 00:28:32.544 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That's too low.</i>
<i>We're going to have to raise it.</i>

536
00:28:32.628 --> 00:28:34.004 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm bypassing
the phase converter.

537
00:28:34.087 --> 00:28:36.340 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Wait. I didn't tell you
to do that.

538
00:28:36.423 --> 00:28:37.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Won't that increase
the field polarity?

539
00:28:38.050 --> 00:28:40.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- <i>Yes, but...</i>
- [coughing]

540
00:28:41.887 --> 00:28:44.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Listen to me carefully.
I want you to try...

541
00:28:44.181 --> 00:28:45.599 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dayla, it's Loken.

542
00:28:45.682 --> 00:28:48.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Take the warp core off-line.
- What are you talking about?

543
00:28:48.518 --> 00:28:52.105 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bypass the driver coil and shunt power
directly to the polaron matrix.

544
00:28:53.482 --> 00:28:55.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[coughing]

545
00:29:02.366 --> 00:29:04.034 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The cloak is back on line.

546
00:29:04.117 --> 00:29:05.452 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Get us out of here,
full impulse.

547
00:29:06.370 --> 00:29:09.831 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dayla, secure the Engineering section
and get back to the Bridge.

548
00:29:11.667 --> 00:29:13.585 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dayla!

549
00:29:16.088 --> 00:29:18.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm not reading
any life signs in Engineering.

550
00:29:30.602 --> 00:29:33.021 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Dayla?
- She's dead.

551
00:29:33.105 --> 00:29:34.147 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How's Seven?

552
00:29:35.399 --> 00:29:36.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She may be in shock.

553
00:29:36.984 --> 00:29:38.026 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not sure.

554
00:29:39.820 --> 00:29:40.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have a look.

555
00:29:50.163 --> 00:29:52.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your opinion, Doctor?

556
00:29:53.041 --> 00:29:55.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I believe
she may be in shock.

557
00:29:56.962 --> 00:29:58.964 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you think we should give her
a cortical stimulant?

558
00:29:59.047 --> 00:30:01.008 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That might be indicated.

559
00:30:03.635 --> 00:30:04.970 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You are no doctor, are you?

560
00:30:07.431 --> 00:30:09.057 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You and I need to talk...

561
00:30:09.141 --> 00:30:10.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
alone.

562
00:30:19.401 --> 00:30:21.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What the hell is going on?

563
00:30:21.403 --> 00:30:23.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't know
what you mean.

564
00:30:23.113 --> 00:30:25.699 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nothing about this mission
is adding up.

565
00:30:25.782 --> 00:30:27.701 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's obvious
you know a lot more

566
00:30:27.784 --> 00:30:29.828 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
about cloaking systems
than biology.

567
00:30:29.911 --> 00:30:31.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So did Dayla.

568
00:30:31.121 --> 00:30:33.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And the second
our cloak failed,

569
00:30:33.332 --> 00:30:36.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
half a dozen Annari warships
came after us--

570
00:30:36.460 --> 00:30:39.838 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
one little medical transport.

571
00:30:39.921 --> 00:30:41.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The truth!

572
00:30:44.551 --> 00:30:48.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My colleagues and I have
been working at a secret base

573
00:30:48.305 --> 00:30:49.806 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but not to create vaccines.

574
00:30:50.724 --> 00:30:53.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We've been developing
cloaking devices for our fleet.

575
00:30:53.727 --> 00:30:55.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This ship is a prototype.

576
00:30:55.354 --> 00:30:57.272 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Annari know we have it,

577
00:30:57.356 --> 00:30:59.024 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and they don't want us
to get it home.

578
00:30:59.107 --> 00:31:00.484 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I never would have agreed to this

579
00:31:00.567 --> 00:31:02.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if I had known
you had a military objective.

580
00:31:02.778 --> 00:31:06.239 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our world has been under
an Annari blockade for three years.

581
00:31:07.366 --> 00:31:10.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The planet is protected
by a shield grid,

582
00:31:10.118 --> 00:31:13.622 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but it's almost impossible
to get our ships in or out.

583
00:31:13.705 --> 00:31:16.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I convinced Captain Janeway
this was a humanitarian mission.

584
00:31:16.625 --> 00:31:17.918 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It is.

585
00:31:18.835 --> 00:31:22.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Annari are choking us
to death slowly.

586
00:31:22.547 --> 00:31:25.509 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If we can't get supply ships
through the blockade,

587
00:31:25.592 --> 00:31:27.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we can't get food
to our people...

588
00:31:28.428 --> 00:31:30.013 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
or medicine.

589
00:31:31.431 --> 00:31:34.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
For all I know,
that's another lie.

590
00:31:37.312 --> 00:31:38.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[door shuts]

591
00:31:41.400 --> 00:31:42.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Reverse course.

592
00:31:42.526 --> 00:31:43.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sir?

593
00:31:43.652 --> 00:31:46.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- We're heading back to Voyager.
- I don't understand.

594
00:31:46.446 --> 00:31:47.948 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He knows about the cloak.

595
00:31:49.157 --> 00:31:50.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I would've told you...

596
00:31:50.450 --> 00:31:52.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- I gave you an order.
- What about the mission?

597
00:31:52.369 --> 00:31:53.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's not your concern.

598
00:31:53.703 --> 00:31:56.081 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You want to be a starship officer?
Your job is to follow orders.

599
00:31:56.164 --> 00:31:58.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Sir, I don't think you...
- This is not a debate.

600
00:31:58.667 --> 00:32:00.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're under my command.

601
00:32:07.342 --> 00:32:08.385 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, sir.

602
00:32:08.468 --> 00:32:10.095 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not anymore.

603
00:32:10.178 --> 00:32:11.471 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're relieved.

604
00:32:11.555 --> 00:32:12.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You, take the helm.

605
00:32:14.474 --> 00:32:16.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I believe you're the one
who's been relieved.

606
00:32:21.648 --> 00:32:23.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[humming]

607
00:32:25.277 --> 00:32:27.112 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Where are you going
in such a hurry?

608
00:32:27.195 --> 00:32:28.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Engineering,
to assist B'Elanna...

609
00:32:30.323 --> 00:32:31.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lieutenant Torres.

610
00:32:31.658 --> 00:32:33.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, you've been seeing
a lot of my wife lately.

611
00:32:33.910 --> 00:32:35.537 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Should I be worried?

612
00:32:35.620 --> 00:32:37.164 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mm, the repairs are extensive.

613
00:32:37.247 --> 00:32:39.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- It's a lot of work.
- You can't fool me.

614
00:32:39.541 --> 00:32:42.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I heard you two were planning
on scaling some cliffs together.

615
00:32:42.669 --> 00:32:44.004 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It was her idea.

616
00:32:44.087 --> 00:32:45.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, relax.

617
00:32:45.297 --> 00:32:47.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Spending time on the holodeck
is good for you,

618
00:32:47.674 --> 00:32:50.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but if you really want
to have fun, forget climbing.

619
00:32:50.343 --> 00:32:51.928 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Try my race car program.

620
00:32:52.012 --> 00:32:53.138 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Race car"?

621
00:32:53.221 --> 00:32:56.641 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You get to chase me around a track
in an old Earth ground vehicle.

622
00:32:56.725 --> 00:32:58.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
300 kph.

623
00:32:58.351 --> 00:32:59.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It'll really get
your blood pumping.

624
00:33:00.812 --> 00:33:02.731 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are you challenging me
to a competition?

625
00:33:02.814 --> 00:33:04.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, you think
you can take me?

626
00:33:05.025 --> 00:33:07.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Tomorrow, Holodeck 2,
1900 hours.

627
00:33:22.876 --> 00:33:25.587 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There is something
we need to discuss.

628
00:33:25.670 --> 00:33:28.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sure, as soon as you help me
finish this diagnostic.

629
00:33:28.381 --> 00:33:30.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- I can't do this.
- Of course you can.

630
00:33:30.383 --> 00:33:33.512 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- You've done dozens of them.
- I'm not talking about the diagnostic.

631
00:33:33.595 --> 00:33:35.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- I'm talking about us.
- "Us"?

632
00:33:35.514 --> 00:33:38.642 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your interest in me--
it's inappropriate.

633
00:33:39.643 --> 00:33:41.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't think I understand.

634
00:33:41.478 --> 00:33:44.147 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's obvious you desire
a romantic involvement.

635
00:33:44.231 --> 00:33:45.690 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Excuse me?

636
00:33:45.774 --> 00:33:47.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've made all
the customary overtures--

637
00:33:47.651 --> 00:33:49.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
finding reasons
to spend time with me,

638
00:33:49.819 --> 00:33:51.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
complimenting me,

639
00:33:51.363 --> 00:33:54.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
inviting me to engage
in recreational activities.

640
00:33:54.699 --> 00:33:57.869 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your husband even challenged me
to a ritual contest.

641
00:33:57.953 --> 00:33:59.579 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you talking about?

642
00:33:59.663 --> 00:34:02.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
According to my research,
it's a traditional Klingon practice.

643
00:34:02.457 --> 00:34:06.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look... I'm sorry,
but you've got the wrong idea.

644
00:34:06.670 --> 00:34:08.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You seemed a little lonely.

645
00:34:08.547 --> 00:34:10.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was just trying to be friendly.

646
00:34:10.882 --> 00:34:13.051 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- I scanned you.
- You scanned me?

647
00:34:13.134 --> 00:34:14.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In the Jefferies tube.

648
00:34:14.261 --> 00:34:16.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your blood pressure
and neurotransmitter readings

649
00:34:16.471 --> 00:34:18.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
indicated a state of arousal.

650
00:34:18.515 --> 00:34:21.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was hot, and I've been
under a lot of pressure,

651
00:34:21.977 --> 00:34:24.396 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I certainly
wasn't aroused.

652
00:34:26.648 --> 00:34:28.942 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Look, Icheb, I like you...

653
00:34:29.025 --> 00:34:34.072 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but aside from the fact
that I am a much older woman,

654
00:34:34.155 --> 00:34:35.240 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm married.

655
00:34:35.824 --> 00:34:37.826 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's why we have to do
the honorable thing.

656
00:34:39.160 --> 00:34:40.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We should stop seeing each other.

657
00:34:45.250 --> 00:34:46.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're right.

658
00:34:49.004 --> 00:34:52.674 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As much as it hurts,
I'll just have to face the truth.

659
00:34:52.757 --> 00:34:54.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's for the best.

660
00:34:54.676 --> 00:34:56.011 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mm.

661
00:35:10.692 --> 00:35:12.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[quietly]
Seven?

662
00:35:14.487 --> 00:35:15.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Feeling better?

663
00:35:16.698 --> 00:35:18.617 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well enough to return to duty.

664
00:35:18.700 --> 00:35:21.995 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You won't be returning to duty,
not on this ship anyway.

665
00:35:23.496 --> 00:35:25.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Loken lied to us.

666
00:35:25.498 --> 00:35:26.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There's no vaccine.

667
00:35:27.375 --> 00:35:29.169 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The cloak is the real cargo.

668
00:35:30.253 --> 00:35:33.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I ordered the crew to take us
back to Voyager, but they refused.

669
00:35:34.966 --> 00:35:36.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They mutinied.

670
00:35:36.509 --> 00:35:38.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I guess that's what you'd call it.

671
00:35:39.679 --> 00:35:41.640 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've packed some supplies.

672
00:35:41.723 --> 00:35:42.891 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We'll take an escape pod.

673
00:35:42.974 --> 00:35:45.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm hoping the Annari
will leave us alone,

674
00:35:45.644 --> 00:35:46.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
treat us as neutral parties.

675
00:35:46.895 --> 00:35:49.022 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're not "neutral parties."

676
00:35:49.105 --> 00:35:51.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is a military mission.
We can't get involved.

677
00:35:51.733 --> 00:35:54.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We've been "involved" since
you first fired on that Annari ship.

678
00:35:54.778 --> 00:35:57.155 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought I was helping people
in distress.

679
00:35:57.238 --> 00:35:59.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't they still need your help?

680
00:35:59.699 --> 00:36:01.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you abandoning this ship

681
00:36:01.201 --> 00:36:03.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because the mission
wasn't what you expected

682
00:36:03.370 --> 00:36:06.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
or because being a Captain
wasn't what you expected?

683
00:36:06.831 --> 00:36:09.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I am perfectly capable
of commanding a starship.

684
00:36:09.334 --> 00:36:10.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you?

685
00:36:10.752 --> 00:36:12.504 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Clearly, you're uncomfortable
with the role--

686
00:36:12.587 --> 00:36:14.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
delegating tasks, giving orders.

687
00:36:14.422 --> 00:36:16.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Someone died
following my orders!

688
00:36:16.341 --> 00:36:18.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can't blame yourself
for that.

689
00:36:18.218 --> 00:36:20.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A Captain's responsible
for the lives of his crew.

690
00:36:20.637 --> 00:36:25.100 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
People sometimes die on missions,
despite the Captain's best efforts.

691
00:36:25.934 --> 00:36:28.436 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I should have stuck
to playing Buster Kincaid.

692
00:36:29.145 --> 00:36:33.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A holodeck program can be turned off
when it no longer suits you.

693
00:36:33.149 --> 00:36:34.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Reality can't.

694
00:36:40.073 --> 00:36:42.492 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you really feel responsible
for this crew,

695
00:36:42.575 --> 00:36:45.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
you'll help them get home,

696
00:36:45.203 --> 00:36:47.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because they won't survive
without you.

697
00:36:53.545 --> 00:36:55.630 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Is that some new kind
of weapon?

698
00:36:55.714 --> 00:36:59.175 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They're scanning pulses
designed to illuminate cloaked ships.

699
00:36:59.259 --> 00:37:01.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If we hit one,
we'll be exposed.

700
00:37:01.553 --> 00:37:03.054 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How are we going
to get through?

701
00:37:03.138 --> 00:37:04.347 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We'll find a way.

702
00:37:05.849 --> 00:37:07.267 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought you were leaving.

703
00:37:07.350 --> 00:37:10.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I get claustrophobic
in escape pods.

704
00:37:10.311 --> 00:37:13.106 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Switch to manual helm control.
Full power to shields.

705
00:37:16.693 --> 00:37:18.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Aye, Captain.

706
00:37:23.491 --> 00:37:24.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

707
00:37:33.501 --> 00:37:35.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Two Annari ships
have entered orbit.

708
00:37:35.587 --> 00:37:37.088 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- They are hailing.
- On screen.

709
00:37:37.714 --> 00:37:40.842 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain Geral, we have
12 isotons of ore for you.

710
00:37:40.925 --> 00:37:43.845 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm under orders to escort you
out of Annari space,

711
00:37:43.928 --> 00:37:45.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
immediately.

712
00:37:45.513 --> 00:37:47.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've been
supporting our enemy.

713
00:37:47.098 --> 00:37:48.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You must be mistaken.

714
00:37:48.516 --> 00:37:50.977 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A shuttlecraft
matching your hull composition

715
00:37:51.060 --> 00:37:53.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
fired on one of our ships
several days ago.

716
00:37:53.855 --> 00:37:55.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And we recently detected
two human bio-signatures

717
00:37:55.940 --> 00:37:57.859 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
on a Kraylor warship.

718
00:37:57.942 --> 00:37:59.944 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- I can explain that.
- If you don't leave immediately,

719
00:38:00.028 --> 00:38:01.863 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
we'll be forced to fire on you.

720
00:38:01.946 --> 00:38:04.449 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our warp drive
is still being repaired.

721
00:38:04.532 --> 00:38:06.493 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then we'll escort you at impulse.

722
00:38:07.452 --> 00:38:09.496 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You have five minutes
to lift off.

723
00:38:11.748 --> 00:38:13.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So much for our new
deuterium injectors.

724
00:38:13.583 --> 00:38:15.335 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What about Harry and Seven?

725
00:38:15.418 --> 00:38:16.544 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Janeway]
We'll go looking for them,

726
00:38:16.628 --> 00:38:19.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
as soon as we get rid
of our escort.

727
00:38:26.429 --> 00:38:28.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Evasive maneuvers.

728
00:38:29.682 --> 00:38:32.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- There are too many of them.
- You're doing fine.

729
00:38:32.393 --> 00:38:35.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just try to stay at least 100 meters
ahead of the closest pulse.

730
00:38:35.313 --> 00:38:36.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

731
00:38:38.274 --> 00:38:39.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We should return fire.

732
00:38:39.734 --> 00:38:43.154 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, that would only give them
another way to triangulate our position.

733
00:38:47.242 --> 00:38:48.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Our shields are failing.

734
00:38:48.910 --> 00:38:51.496 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're losing structural integrity
on the lower decks.

735
00:38:51.579 --> 00:38:53.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Reroute emergency power.

736
00:38:54.457 --> 00:38:55.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's insufficient.

737
00:38:56.084 --> 00:38:58.169 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Open a channel
to the lead Annari ship.

738
00:38:58.253 --> 00:39:00.255 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Sir?
- Do it.

739
00:39:02.173 --> 00:39:03.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Aye, sir.

740
00:39:05.885 --> 00:39:08.930 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is Captain Kim of
the Kraylor Vessel Nightingale.

741
00:39:09.013 --> 00:39:11.474 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm prepared to discuss terms
for our surrender.

742
00:39:12.851 --> 00:39:13.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
End transmission.

743
00:39:13.977 --> 00:39:15.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We trusted you.

744
00:39:15.937 --> 00:39:17.272 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you still should.

745
00:39:17.355 --> 00:39:18.439 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're responding.

746
00:39:19.524 --> 00:39:21.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't have time to explain.
On screen.

747
00:39:23.278 --> 00:39:25.780 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your surrender
will be unconditional.

748
00:39:25.864 --> 00:39:27.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, it won't.

749
00:39:27.407 --> 00:39:29.909 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Either you allow my crew
to evacuate to the surface,

750
00:39:29.993 --> 00:39:31.828 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
or I'll put this ship
on self-destruct.

751
00:39:32.579 --> 00:39:34.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You'll never get
the cloaking technology.

752
00:39:34.622 --> 00:39:37.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Something tells me your superiors
won't be happy about that.

753
00:39:38.877 --> 00:39:41.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your crew will be taken
aboard my vessel

754
00:39:41.212 --> 00:39:42.964 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and brought
to an Annari detention center.

755
00:39:43.047 --> 00:39:45.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My crew is going to the surface
in escape pods.

756
00:39:45.592 --> 00:39:49.429 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Once they're clear, you can lock on
to this ship with a tractor beam.

757
00:39:51.264 --> 00:39:52.473 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Agreed.

758
00:39:52.557 --> 00:39:54.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You've two minutes to evacuate.

759
00:39:55.977 --> 00:39:57.604 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I will not abandon this ship.

760
00:39:58.688 --> 00:40:01.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm glad to hear that,
because I'm going to need you here.

761
00:40:01.566 --> 00:40:03.776 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Get your people into
the pods... quickly.

762
00:40:03.860 --> 00:40:05.028 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But the cloak...

763
00:40:05.111 --> 00:40:06.696 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've got a plan to save it.

764
00:40:06.779 --> 00:40:09.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If I fail, at least
the scientist who designed it

765
00:40:09.282 --> 00:40:10.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
will be alive
to create another one.

766
00:40:17.165 --> 00:40:19.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Seven, scan the Annari's
tractor emitters.

767
00:40:19.959 --> 00:40:22.128 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I need to know
the exact beam polarity.

768
00:40:22.211 --> 00:40:23.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are we going to do?

769
00:40:23.963 --> 00:40:26.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Once they lock on to us,
they're going to come about

770
00:40:27.008 --> 00:40:28.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and pull us away
from the planet.

771
00:40:28.509 --> 00:40:29.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
As soon as they do,

772
00:40:29.886 --> 00:40:31.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we're going to reverse
our shield polarity.

773
00:40:31.763 --> 00:40:34.307 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If we time it right, it should
give us enough momentum

774
00:40:34.390 --> 00:40:36.267 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to outrun them
to the defense perimeter.

775
00:40:36.351 --> 00:40:38.645 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're going to use their
own weapons against them?

776
00:40:38.728 --> 00:40:40.063 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The escape pods are away.

777
00:40:44.859 --> 00:40:46.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

778
00:40:46.694 --> 00:40:48.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Disengage the cloak.

779
00:40:50.615 --> 00:40:52.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They've locked on.

780
00:40:54.827 --> 00:40:56.037 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sir?

781
00:40:56.120 --> 00:40:57.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not yet.

782
00:40:58.039 --> 00:40:59.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Steady.

783
00:41:01.042 --> 00:41:02.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now!

784
00:41:07.507 --> 00:41:08.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Status?

785
00:41:09.008 --> 00:41:10.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shields are failing.

786
00:41:10.426 --> 00:41:12.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Four Annari vessels
are in pursuit.

787
00:41:12.470 --> 00:41:14.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- They're closing.
- Full thrusters!

788
00:41:14.889 --> 00:41:15.932 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[alarm bleeping]

789
00:41:16.849 --> 00:41:18.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shields are down.

790
00:41:18.476 --> 00:41:20.436 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Get us through that defense
perimeter, Mr. Terek.

791
00:41:20.520 --> 00:41:21.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

792
00:41:30.071 --> 00:41:31.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're inside.

793
00:41:32.240 --> 00:41:34.492 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Annari have
broken off their pursuit.

794
00:41:36.911 --> 00:41:39.330 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Take us to the surface,
Mr. Terek.

795
00:41:51.009 --> 00:41:53.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We've just crossed out
of Annari space.

796
00:41:53.469 --> 00:41:55.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our escorts have broken off.
They're going to warp.

797
00:41:55.847 --> 00:41:57.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bring the long-range sensors
on line.

798
00:41:57.515 --> 00:41:58.933 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You and Tom, take the Flyer.

799
00:41:59.017 --> 00:42:01.519 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Start your search
at Harry's last known position.

800
00:42:01.602 --> 00:42:04.313 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Tuvok, send an encrypted message
to the Kraylor homeworld.

801
00:42:04.397 --> 00:42:06.858 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
See if they know
where Harry and Seven are.

802
00:42:06.941 --> 00:42:08.443 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That won't be necessary,
Captain.

803
00:42:08.526 --> 00:42:10.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ensign Kim is hailing us.

804
00:42:10.486 --> 00:42:11.529 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
From where?

805
00:42:12.071 --> 00:42:13.406 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A cloaked vessel.

806
00:42:13.489 --> 00:42:14.699 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's directly astern.

807
00:42:17.452 --> 00:42:21.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Kim] <i>Acting Captain's Personal Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 54282.5.</i>

808
00:42:21.748 --> 00:42:22.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Final entry.</i>

809
00:42:23.082 --> 00:42:25.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>New cloaking systems are being</i>
<i>installed in other Kraylor ships,</i>

810
00:42:25.960 --> 00:42:28.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>so I guess the mission</i>
<i>was a success.</i>

811
00:42:28.337 --> 00:42:30.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Still, I wish</i>
<i>I felt better about it.</i>

812
00:42:32.967 --> 00:42:34.302 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Welcome home.

813
00:42:35.053 --> 00:42:36.554 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's good to be back.

814
00:42:37.555 --> 00:42:40.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So, what'll it be tonight?

815
00:42:40.558 --> 00:42:42.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have a light
Tula cheese soufflé

816
00:42:42.685 --> 00:42:43.895 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
or a zesty lasagna.

817
00:42:44.645 --> 00:42:47.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, Neelix,
the truth is, I'm not sure.

818
00:42:48.232 --> 00:42:49.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought
we talked about this.

819
00:42:49.817 --> 00:42:53.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- A Captain has to be deci...
- I'm not a Captain, Neelix.

820
00:42:57.325 --> 00:42:59.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not yet, anyway.

